# EPIC 2: Posts & Feed

This epic focuses on enabling users to create posts, view a feed of posts, and handle basic content display.

---

## ðŸ§± Backend Goals

- Define a `Post` model using Prisma.
- Allow users to create posts via authenticated API.
- Provide a feed API that returns recent posts, sorted by time.

---

## ðŸ–¥ Frontend Goals

- Create a simple `feed.html` layout.
- Fetch and display the latest posts using JavaScript.
- Allow users to create new posts with optional image/media.

---

## ðŸ”„ Development Process

Each feature will follow a backend-first development cycle:
1. Design the database schema (Prisma)
2. Create RESTful endpoints in Express
3. Build the corresponding UI in Vanilla JavaScript

